Technical Support Engineer		Olapic		New York City, NY, US		<div class="rich-text" itemprop="description"><strong>Listing Info<br /><br /></strong>Olapic is the leader in visual marketing, providing brands and publishers with tools to engage their audience and support a strong community built on photo and video sharing. Olapic helps companies grow by leveraging the power of data from multiple photo-sharing sites such as Facebook, Twitter, Instagram, and more.<br /><br />Started in 2010 by a group of engineers that met while each completing a MBA at Columbia Business School, Olapic now serves clients such as Alex and Ani, Anthropologie, The North Face, and West Elm. Olapic is a graduate of NYC SeedStart, the winner of the 2010 Columbia University Lang Venture Fund, and has been featured by Mashable, Gigaom, Bostinnovation, and The New York Times. Join this fast growing start-up located in the heart of Flatiron as a Technical Support Engineer and member of the ever-expanding Customer Support Team!<br /><br />The Customer Support Team at Olapic is a critical part of our future success. It is the front line of Olapic’s customer experience, and provides effective, high-quality technical support to our rapidly growing global customer base. The Technical Support Engineer is a natural problem solver who is able to work patiently and efficiently with hundreds of customers, amidst exponential traffic growth and millions of impressions per month as we continuously expand the Olapic Platform. The role will involve supporting both technical and non-technical end users, while also contributing to programming and documentation projects, as required.<br /><br />This is a great position for someone early on in their development career. You’re a recent grad in Computer Science/Engineering without a lot of work experience or you’re a year or two into your professional career and are looking to expand on your technical skill-set in a start-up environment and further develop your client-facing experience.<br /><br /> <br /><br /><strong>Main Responsibilities And Qualifications<br /></strong><ul><li>Extremely strong communication and follow-up skills. You can speak both engineer and human.</li> </ul><ul><li>Speaks and writes English fluently.</li> <li>Self-driven and thrives in a fast-paced environment.</li> </ul><ul><li>Shows initiative; works hard and leads by example as part of a greater team.</li> <li>Brings new ideas to the table about the support process and architecture; is able to implement them if needed!</li> <li>Great organization skills and ability to plan ahead.</li> <li>Is able to automate processes when required.</li> <li>Must be a creative problem solver; able to think outside the box when challenging support issues present themselves.</li> <li>Customer focused mentality required; you love helping other people and see how they make great use of our products.</li> </ul><ul><li>Strong development ability in at least one language, preferably PHP.</li> <li>Experience managing databases, preferably MySQL.</li> <li>Strong understanding of web technologies, including CSS, HTML4/5, and JavaScript.</li> <li>Familiarity with Git.</li> <li>Troubleshooting (especially when time is of the essence).</li> <li>Strong ability to dig through logs and other data sources.</li> <li>Ability to write documentation that other people want to read.</li></ul></div><div class="rich-text" itemprop="description">Olapic increases sales and engagement for over 200+ brands and retailers by integrating customer photos into the shopping experience. <br /><br />Our clients use Olapic to increase conversion and time on site, differentiate the shopping experience, keep content fresh, drive up-sell and cross-sell, lower return rates, and reduce lifestyle content costs.</div>